# 📖 SUPERSPLOIT QUICK-REFERENCE
Main command index. For detailed guides, use help [command].

---

### 🔍 RECONNAISSANCE & DISCOVERY
- search [key]    : Search for exploits, recon modules, or payloads.
- use [mod]       : Load a module into the active context.
- set [k] [v]      : Configure global or module-specific variables.
- show [opt]       : Display info, options, targets, or exploits.
- run              : Execute the currently loaded reconnaissance module.
- suggest          : Auto-suggest exploits based on discovered target data.
- edit profile     : Manually edit persona research and social media data.
- import [type]    : Safely import exploits, payloads, targets, or profiles.
- delete [type]    : Remove an individual profile or target by ID.
- purge [type]     : Wipe entire categories of user data (profiles/targets).
- add profile      : Create a persona from scan results or manual entry.
- up-nmap-db       : Migrate flat nmap-os-db.txt to signatures.db.
- up-service-db    : Migrate flat nmap-service-probes.txt to signatures.db.

### 💥 EXPLOITATION & PAYLOADS
- exploit            : Run the currently loaded exploit module.
- compile            : Cross-compile C source files into binary executables.
- sessions           : List and manage active command-and-control sessions.
- sessions -i [id]   : Interact with an active session by ID.
- generate-apk           : Build a custom Android payload (Native C Injection).
- generate-apk-buildozer : Build a custom Android payload (Kivy/Buildozer pipeline).
- generate-shellcode     : Generate raw, weaponized shellcode for direct injection.
- kaslr                  : Conceptual KASLR slide calculator and kernel base resolver.
- encrypt / decrypt      : Encrypt or decrypt local files using framework keys.

### 📡 C2 INTERACTION (Active Session)
- upload / download : Securely transfer files between local and remote.
- load <path>       : Silently inject a Python payload into target RAM.
- auto_root         : Attempt silent privilege escalation (Magisk/LPE).
- dump_sms / calls  : Exfiltrate SMS messages or call history.
- dump_wifi / chrome: Harvest WiFi passwords, Chrome cookies, and logins.
- dump_google_passwords: Targeted extraction of Google Password Manager data.
- get_location      : Extract last known GPS coordinates.
- shell             : Drop into a native system shell on the target.
- exit              : Terminate the current session.

### ⚙️ SYSTEM & DOCUMENTATION
- workspace        : List, create, or switch between isolated workspaces.
- jobs             : View and terminate background tasks (e.g., listeners).
- vars             : List all configurable framework variables.
- clean            : Wipe temporary files, execution logs, and cache.
- banner           : Display ASCII banner and current configuration status.
- update-info      : Manually trigger a refresh of the exploit cache.
- debugdb          : Display full framework database memory cache.
- shells           : List available terminal shells for threaded handlers.
- android          : Information about android payload configuration.
- payload-types    : Detailed breakdown of Android payload variants.
- help [topic]     : View configuration technical documentation.
- exit             : Safely shut down the SuperSploit framework.

